Q3. What is an attack? Explain the different types of attacks.
Definition of Attack
An attack is an act that exploits a vulnerability to damage or steal information or disrupt services. Attacks can be intentional or unintentional.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


Types of Attacks (From Notes)
1. Malicious Code Attacks
Includes viruses, worms, Trojans, logic bombs, backdoors.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


2. Hoaxes
Fake virus warnings containing actual viruses.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


3. Backdoors / Trapdoors
Secret entry points installed by attackers to bypass security.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


4. Password Attacks
Brute force

Dictionary attack

Password cracking

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


5. Spoofing
Forging identity such as IP address spoofing.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


6. Denial of Service (DoS)
Flooding target with excessive requests.

7. Distributed DoS (DDoS)
DoS from multiple distributed systems.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


8. Man-in-the-Middle Attack
Attacker intercepts communication between two systems.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


9. Spam and Mail Bombing
Unsolicited emails; flooding inbox.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


10. Sniffing
Capturing data packets across networks.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


11. Social Engineering
Attacker manipulates users to reveal sensitive information.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


12. Buffer Overflow
Sending more data than buffer can handle → execute malicious code.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


13. Timing Attacks
Exploiting web browser cache and timing information.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


Case Study – WannaCry Ransomware
Attack type: Malicious code (worm + ransomware)

Exploited Windows SMB vulnerability

Spread to 200,000+ systems

Encrypted data and demanded ransom
Impact: $4–8 billion global loss.

Conclusion
Understanding attack types allows organizations to design layered security controls, deploy intrusion detection systems, and establish incident response strategies.

