1. Summarize the steps involved in the design of Security Architecture. (15 Marks)
Introduction
Security architecture is the blueprint that defines how an organization’s information security program is structured, implemented, and maintained. It ensures that policies, technologies, and procedures work together to protect assets.
Designing a security architecture is systematic and must align with business goals.

Steps in Designing Security Architecture
1. Understand the Organization (Know Yourself)
Identify mission, objectives, and structure.

Identify critical business processes and supporting information systems.

Understand the information flow, data sensitivity, and operational dependencies.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


2. Establish Security Policy Framework
Develop enterprise-wide security policies.

Policies define security goals and user responsibilities.

Includes General Security Policy, Issue-Specific Policy, and System-Specific Policy.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


3. Identify and Classify Information Assets
List all hardware, software, data, people, and network components.

Classify assets as Confidential, Internal, or Public.

Assign values according to criticality and sensitivity.

5 OEC503 INFORMATION SECURITY N…


